						<summary>

						<p>Same wall.</p>						

						<p>The meaning of this inscription is not very clear.</p>						

						<p>It appears to record that the temple trustees <hi rend="italic">(tānattār),</hi> the <hi rend="italic">sabhai</hi> and the <hi rend="italic">ūr</hi> of Śiṟṟiṅgūr a <hi rend="italic">brahmadēyam</hi> in Kuṟukkaik-kūṟṟam in Rājarāja-vaḷanāḍu, agreed to have <hi rend="italic">Parāśivaṉ</hi> in Śiṟṟiṅgur as desired by the <hi rend="italic">Parāśivar</hi> of Tiruvadigai, Tiruttuṟai, Tiruveṇṇainallūr, Tiruvōmāttūr and Tirumudukuṉṟam, all in Naḍuvil-maṇḍalam. </p>						

						</summary>
